" 0 "" {TEXT 233 121 "From the definition of chaos as 'sensitive depen
dence to initial conditions' it would seem that this is chaotic behavi
or." }{TEXT 233 0 "" }}{PARA 269 "" 0 "" {TEXT 233 148 "However, the L
yapunov exponents are negative during the oscillation and zero during \+
kicks. Only near deltadot=0 will nearby trajectories be strongly" }
{TEXT 233 0 "" }}{PARA 269 "" 0 "" {TEXT 233 122 "divergent, but that \+
will only happen when the system is seeking an equilibrium. All and al
l, it seems most appropriate to " }{TEXT 233 12 "call this a " }{TEXT 
233 0 "" }}{PARA 269 "" 0 "" {TEXT 233 91 "non-linear system with frac
tal basins of attraction, as shown in Figure 2 of the exercises." }
{TEXT 233 0 "" }}{PARA 269 "" 0 "" {TEXT 233 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 269 
